    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make it law that any veteran of HM Armed Forces be given priority for housing.",
        "additional_details": "Portsmouth city council has already adopted this policy after the Armed Forces Act made provision for giving Veterans specific privileges. To honour the armed forces covenant Parliament must impose a duty on all local authorities to place homeless veterans at the head of the queue for housing.\r\n\r\nNone who serve should suffer the indignity of homelessness. When we see how veterans are forgotten, there is little wonder why recruitment is so low.",
        "background": "The British Legion has estimated that there are currently about 6,000 homeless veterans in the UK. Many of them are suffering PTSD and other mental health problems following combat, or struggle to adjust to independent living after service.\r\n\r\nThose who serve should be supported, not abandoned.",
